{
  "stem": "24259.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I believe they usually kind of tried to shame the religious people that had-- like rabbis who had beards, they would shave their beards, and the long sideburns that religious Jews wear, they would cut those down, I'm told.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Just to show them, humiliate them, in front of their-- their flock.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I believe it was 1942.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "About a year after we got in, my father had somehow gotten some information about some digging that was going on outside the ghetto that the Germans claimed were to be used for storing potatoes for the winter.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "However, somehow, some information that my father had gathered, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] as it turned out later on, it was true that it turned out to be the grave, the mass grave for the people in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But my father was able to smuggle my mother and myself out just a few days prior to when they killed everyone in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Most of my mother's family and most of my father's family were all killed during that time.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And some of them also escaped from the ghetto, but were later caught and also killed.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Most of our family died from both sides in-- in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "None from my mother's family.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She was the only survivor.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "However, my father did have one sister and one brother survive.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And in total, there were seven brothers and sisters in my father's family.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And of course, three survived and four died.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Also, my father's mother, my grandmother, was also killed during that time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Mostly through my father and my mother telling me this.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And of course, the people that survived I knew and lived with throughout the years later.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Correct.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
